# Logic-Code-Deployment Trace Rule

When the user asks for architecture traceability, build this chain:

```text
Use Case / Scenario
-> Logical element
-> Code element
-> Build element
-> Delivery element
-> Deployment element
-> Runtime interaction
```

Relationship semantics:

- Code element -> logical element: `Manifest`.
- Build element -> code element: `Build From`.
- Delivery target contains build output or external software: `Composition` or `Aggregation`.
- Delivery or executable target -> deployment element: `Deployed To`.
- Deployment communication path: `CommunicationPath`.

Flag gaps:

- Logical element has no code Manifest.
- Code element maps to multiple logical elements without explanation.
- Repo exists but is not configured.
- Build target has no Build From source.
- Delivery target contains no build output.
- Deployable artifact has no deployment target.
- Runtime interaction references a missing logical element.

Output a trace table:

```text
Scenario | Logical element | Code | Build output | Delivery target | Deployment target | Runtime note | Gaps
```
